info.title: Housing Metrics API
info.description: The Parcl Labs API provides analytics on the U.S. housing market, including data on housing stock, sales, listings, rentals, investor activity, and market trends.

get.description: Gets a list of unique identifiers (<parcl_id>) for markets that correspond to specific keywords or parameters defined by the user. The <parcl_id> is key to navigating the Parcl Labs API, serving as the core mechanism for retrieving market-level information.

parameters.name: query

schema.description: User's search criteria, used to filter <parcl_id>s where the market name meets the specified search criteria
schema.title: Query

parameters.description: User's search criteria, used to filter <parcl_id>s where the market name meets the specified search criteria

parameters.name: location_type

schema.description: Specifies the type of geographic boundary used to filter search results. This field allows users to narrow down search results to specific geographic levels
schema.title: LocationType

parameters.description: Specifies the type of geographic boundary used to filter search results. This field allows users to narrow down search results to specific geographic levels

parameters.name: region

schema.description: Specifies the region of the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific large geographic areas, aligning with common federal statistical divisions
schema.title: RegionType

parameters.description: Specifies the region of the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific large geographic areas, aligning with common federal statistical divisions

parameters.name: state_abbreviation

schema.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific states, using standard state abbreviations
schema.title: StateAbbreviationType

parameters.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific states, using standard state abbreviations

parameters.name: state_fips_code

schema.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results, using the Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) code for geographic identification
schema.title: StateFipsType

parameters.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results, using the Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) code for geographic identification

parameters.name: parcl_id

schema.description: A unique id for a given geographic market in the Parcl Labs API. Parcl_ids are unique and independent of each other, without any hierarchical structure. For example, the parcl_id for Brooklyn, NY bears no relationship to the parcl_id for the New York Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), even though Brooklyn is a part of the New York MSA
schema.title: Parcl Id

parameters.description: A unique id for a given geographic market in the Parcl Labs API. Parcl_ids are unique and independent of each other, without any hierarchical structure. For example, the parcl_id for Brooklyn, NY bears no relationship to the parcl_id for the New York Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), even though Brooklyn is a part of the New York MSA

parameters.name: geoid

schema.description: Specifies the Geographic Identifier (GEOID) used to filter search results. GEOIDs are unique codes assigned to various geographic entities by the U.S. Census Bureau. The Parcl Labs API currently supports GEOIDs for Census zip codes, counties, places, and metros, which range from 5-7 digits in length. For more information, please visit: <https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/geography/guidance/geo-identifiers.html>
schema.title: Geoid

parameters.description: Specifies the Geographic Identifier (GEOID) used to filter search results. GEOIDs are unique codes assigned to various geographic entities by the U.S. Census Bureau. The Parcl Labs API currently supports GEOIDs for Census zip codes, counties, places, and metros, which range from 5-7 digits in length. For more information, please visit: <https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/geography/guidance/geo-identifiers.html>

parameters.name: sort_by

schema.description: Specifies the sorting order for <parcl_id> results. Allows users to sort markets by population size, median income, and other market types
schema.title: SearchSortByType

parameters.description: Specifies the sorting order for <parcl_id> results. Allows users to sort markets by population size, median income, and other market types

parameters.name: sort_order

schema.description: Specifies the direction of the sorting for <parcl_id> results. For example, use sort_order desc with population_size to list more populous markets first.
schema.title: SearchSortOrderType

parameters.description: Specifies the direction of the sorting for <parcl_id> results. For example, use sort_order desc with population_size to list more populous markets first.

schema.description: Page size limit
schema.title: Limit

parameters.description: Page size limit

schema.description: Page offset
schema.title: Offset

parameters.description: Page offset

parcl_id.title: Parcl Id
parcl_id.description: A unique id for a given geographic market in the Parcl Labs API. Parcl_ids are unique and independent of each other, without any hierarchical structure. For example, the parcl_id for Brooklyn, NY bears no relationship to the parcl_id for the New York Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), even though Brooklyn is a part of the New York MSA

country.title: Country
country.description: The country associated with the given <parcl_id>

geoid.title: Geoid
geoid.description: Specifies the Geographic Identifier (GEOID) used to filter search results. GEOIDs are unique codes assigned to various geographic entities by the U.S. Census Bureau, encompassing a wide range of geographic levels from states to census blocks

state_fips_code.title: State Fips Code
state_fips_code.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results, using the Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) code for geographic identification

name.title: Name
name.description: The official name of the market associated with the given <parcl_id>

state_abbreviation.title: State Abbreviation
state_abbreviation.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific states, using standard state abbreviations

region.title: Region
region.description: Specifies the region of the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific large geographic areas, aligning with common federal statistical divisions

location_type.title: Location Type
location_type.description: Specifies the type of geographic boundary used to filter search results. This field allows users to narrow down search results to specific geographic levels

total_population.title: Total Population
total_population.description: The total number of individuals residing within the geographic area identified by the parcl_id. This value is an integer that reflects the latest population count available from relevant census data

median_income.title: Median Income
median_income.description: The median income level of households within the geographic area identified by the parcl_id. This value is an integer representing the latest median household income available from relevant census data

parcl_exchange_market.title: Parcl Exchange Market
parcl_exchange_market.description: Specifies whether the geographic area identified by the parcl_id is available as a tradable real estate market on the Parcl Protocol trading platform. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates that the market is active for trading, while 0 indicates it is not

pricefeed_market.title: Pricefeed Market
pricefeed_market.description: Specifies whether a Parcl Labs price feed is available for the geographic area identified by the <parcl_id>. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates that a price feed is active for that market, while 0 indicates that it is not

case_shiller_10_market.title: Case Shiller 10 Market
case_shiller_10_market.description: Specifies whether the geographic area identified by the parcl_id is included in the Case-Shiller 10 index, which tracks the performance of residential real estate in 10 major metropolitan areas in the United States. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates inclusion in the index, while 0 indicates it is not included

case_shiller_20_market.title: Case Shiller 20 Market
case_shiller_20_market.description: Specifies whether the geographic area identified by the parcl_id is included in the Case-Shiller 20 index, which tracks the performance of residential real estate in 20 major metropolitan areas in the United States. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates inclusion in the index, while 0 indicates it is not included

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in format YYYY-MM-DD. Data reflects the full month indicated by the date (YYYY-MM-DD), with updates on the 15th of the second month following the indicated month to include all events from the specified month. For example, data for January (‘2024-01-01’) is available on March 15th to include January’s events. On the 15th of each month, data is revised to incorporate any new events recorded for the specified month after the initial update, ensuring the most accurate reflection of events.

standard_deviation.title: HousingEventPriceDetailSchema

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods.

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

end_date.description: Specifies the end of the query period, inclusive, in ISO 8601 format, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. Defaults to NULL

parcl_id.title: Parcl Id
parcl_id.description: A unique id for a given geographic market in the Parcl Labs API. Parcl_ids are unique and independent of each other, without any hierarchical structure. For example, the parcl_id for Brooklyn, NY bears no relationship to the parcl_id for the New York Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), even though Brooklyn is a part of the New York MSA

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods.

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

count.description: Count of unique investor-owned properties newly listed for sale

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

purchase_to_sale_ratio.title: Purchase To Sale Ratio
purchase_to_sale_ratio.description:
Investor purchase to sale ratio within a given month, calculated by dividing the number of investor purchases (acquisitions) by the number of investor sales (dispositions).

1.00: Equal numbers of purchases and sales, achieving a 1:1 balance

>1.00: More purchases than sales

<1.00: More sales than purchases

0: No purchases (numerator = 0)

NULL: No sales (denominator = 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

count.description: Count of investor-owned single family properties newly listed for rent, segmented by portfolio size

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

For example, the parcl_id for Brooklyn, NY bears no relationship to the parcl_id for the New York Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), even though Brooklyn is a part of the New York MSA

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

count.description: Count of investor-owned single family properties newly listed for sale, segmented by portfolio size

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

post.description: Gets unit-level properties and their housing event history, including sales, listings, and rentals. The response includes detailed property information and historical event data for each specified property. A maximum of 10000 parcl_property_ids can be requested in a single POST request.

parcl_property_id.title: Parcl Property Id
parcl_property_id.description: Unique property identifier tied to a specific address and unit

event_type.description: Type of housing event associated with the property: SALE, LISTING, RENTAL
event_type.title: PropertyEventType

entity_owner_name.title: Entity Owner Name
entity_owner_name.description:
The name of the entity that owns the property at the time of the event, if owned by a named large-scale operator.

Possible values include:

AMH

TRICON

INVITATION_HOMES

HOME_PARTNERS_OF_AMERICA

PROGRESS_RESIDENTIAL

FIRSTKEY_HOMES

AMHERST

NULL indicates the property is not currently owned by one of these named entities

start_date.title: Start Date
start_date.description: Specifies the beginning of the query period, inclusive, in ISO 8601 format, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. Defaults to NULL

end_date.title: End Date
end_date.description: Specifies the end of the query period, inclusive, in ISO 8601 format, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. Defaults to NULL

parcl_property_id.title: Parcl Property Id
parcl_property_id.description: Unique property identifier tied to a specific address and unit

event_date.title: Event Date
event_date.description: Specific date the housing event occurred on

event_type.title: Event Type
event_type.description: Type of housing event associated with the property: SALE, LISTING, RENTAL, ALL

event_name.title: Event Name
event_name.description:
Subcategory of event_type, providing more specific details about the transaction event
* Sale event names:
  - SOLD: Transactions conducted at fair market value between unrelated parties
  - NON_ARMS_LENGTH_TRANSFER: Transfers where the buyer and seller share a pre-existing relationship (i.e., identical last names) or the transaction is not conducted at fair market value (price is 0 and not in a Non-Disclosure (ND) state)
  - SOLD_INTER_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER: Transactions between two distinct entities
  - NON_ARMS_LENGTH_INTRA_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER: Transfers within the same entity portfolio
* Listing event names: LISTED_SALE, LISTING_REMOVED, OTHER, PENDING_SALE, PRICE_CHANGE, RELISTED
* Rental event names: LISTED_FOR_RENT, PRICE_CHANGE, DELISTED_FOR_RENT

price.title: Price
price.description: Total transactional price for a housing event. For rentals, the price represents the monthly rate

owner_occupied_flag.title: Owner Occupied Flag
owner_occupied_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the property is owner-occupied (i.e., not owned by an investor) at the time of the housing event.

0 signifies that the property is not owner-occupied

1 signifies that the property is owner-occupied

NULL signifies that the owner status is unknown

new_construction_flag.title: New Construction Flag
new_construction_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the property is new construction at the time of the housing event.

0 signifies that the property is not new construction

1 signifies that the property is new construction

investor_flag.title: Investor Flag
investor_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the property is owned by an investor at the time of the event.

0 signifies that the property is not investor-owned

1 signifies that the property is investor-owned

NULL signifies that the investor status is unknown

entity_owner_name.title: Entity Owner Name
entity_owner_name.description:
The name of the entity that owns the property at the time of the event, if owned by a named large-scale operator.

Possible values include:

AMH

TRICON

INVITATION_HOMES

HOME_PARTNERS_OF_AMERICA

PROGRESS_RESIDENTIAL

FIRSTKEY_HOMES

AMHERST

NULL indicates the property is not currently owned by one of these named entities

current_owner_flag.title: Current Owner Flag
current_owner_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the current owner is the owner of the property at the time of the event

0 signifies that the current owner is not the owner at the time of the event

1 signifies that the current owner is the owner at the time of the event

NULL signifies that the ownership status is unknown

transfer_index.title: Transfer Index
transfer_index.description:
Number of transfers that have occurred over the lifetime of a property at the time of the event. Transfers include any SALE event, which includes:
- SOLD
- NON_ARMS_LENGTH_TRANSFER
- SOLD_INTER_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER
- NON_ARMS_LENGTH_INTRA_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER

true_sale_index.title: True Sale Index
true_sale_index.description: Number of genuine property sales that results in an actual change of ownership under fair market conditions (SOLD) that have occurred over the lifetime of a property at the time of the event

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods.

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

parcl_id.title: Parcl Id

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in format YYYY-MM-DD. Data reflects the full month indicated by the date (YYYY-MM-DD), with updates on the 15th of the following month to include all events from the previous month. For example, data for January ('2024-01-01') is available on February 15th to include January's events. On the 15th of each month, data is revised to incorporate any new events recorded for the specified month after the initial update, ensuring the most accurate reflection of events

pct_gross_yield.title: Pct Gross Yield
pct_gross_yield.description:
Percent gross yield within a given month, calculated by dividing the annual median rental income (monthly median new_rental_listing price × 12) by the median new_listings_for_sale price, then multiplying by 100 to convert the result into a percentage

NULL: insufficient data

On the 15th of each month, data is revised to incorporate any new events recorded for the specified month after the initial update, ensuring the most accurate reflection of events.

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

count.description: Count of unique investor-owned properties newly listed for sale

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

purchase_to_sale_ratio.title: Purchase To Sale Ratio
purchase_to_sale_ratio.description:
Investor purchase to sale ratio within a given month, calculated by dividing the number of investor purchases (acquisitions) by the number of investor sales (dispositions).

1.00: Equal numbers of purchases and sales, achieving a 1:1 balance

>1.00: More purchases than sales

<1.00: More sales than purchases

0: No purchases (numerator = 0)

NULL: No sales (denominator = 0)

pct_volatility.title: Pct Volatility
pct_volatility.description: Calculates price feed volatility by determining daily returns of the price feed, applying a rolling standard deviation tailored to market specifics, and annualizing this measure to estimate annual investment volatility. This metric assesses the degree of variation from the average return expressed as a percentage, offering a risk assessment tool for real estate market investors and analysts

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

count.description: Count of unique investor-owned properties newly listed for sale

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

purchase_to_sale_ratio.title: Purchase To Sale Ratio
purchase_to_sale_ratio.description:
Investor purchase to sale ratio within a given month, calculated by dividing the number of investor purchases (acquisitions) by the number of investor sales (dispositions).

1.00: Equal numbers of purchases and sales, achieving a 1:1 balance

>1.00: More purchases than sales

<1.00: More sales than purchases

0: No purchases (numerator = 0)

NULL: No sales (denominator = 0)

For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in format YYYY-MM-DD. Data reflects the full month indicated by the date (YYYY-MM-DD), with updates on the 15th of the following month to include all events from the previous month. For example, data for January ('2024-01-01') is available on February 15th to include January's events. On the 15th of each month, data is revised to incorporate any new events recorded for the specified month after the initial update, ensuring the most accurate reflection of events

rental_units.title: Rental Units
rental_units.description: Total number of units considered a rental, inferred from ownership and rental market activity, within a specified <parcl_id>

total_units.title: Total Units
total_units.description: Total number of single_family, townhouse, condo, and other non-land units within a specified <parcl_id>

pct_rental_concentration.title: Pct Rental Concentration
pct_rental_concentration.description: Percentage of total housing units that are considered rental units within a given month, calculated by dividing the number of rental_units by the total_units, then multiplying by 100 to convert this number into a percentage. This metric estimates the rental concentration within a specified <parcl_id> and may potentially overestimate the actual figure

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day

For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

parcl_id.title: Parcl Id
parcl_id.description: A unique id for a given geographic market in the Parcl Labs API. Parcl_ids are unique and independent of each other, without any hierarchical structure. For example, the parcl_id for Brooklyn, NY bears no relationship to the parcl_id for the New York Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), even though Brooklyn is a part of the New York MSA

country.title: Country
country.description: The country associated with the given <parcl_id>

geoid.title: Geoid
geoid.description: Specifies the Geographic Identifier (GEOID) used to filter search results. GEOIDs are unique codes assigned to various geographic entities by the U.S. Census Bureau, encompassing a wide range of geographic levels from states to census blocks

state_fips_code.title: State Fips Code
state_fips_code.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results, using the Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) code for geographic identification

name.title: Name
name.description: The official name of the market associated with the given <parcl_id>

state_abbreviation.title: State Abbreviation
state_abbreviation.description: Specifies the state within the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific states, using standard state abbreviations

region.title: Region
region.description: Specifies the region of the United States used to filter search results. This field is designed to help users focus their search within specific large geographic areas, aligning with common federal statistical divisions

location_type.title: Location Type
location_type.description: Specifies the type of geographic boundary used to filter search results. This field allows users to narrow down search results to specific geographic levels

total_population.title: Total Population
total_population.description: The total number of individuals residing within the geographic area identified by the parcl_id. This value is an integer that reflects the latest population count available from relevant census data

median_income.title: Median Income
median_income.description: The median income level of households within the geographic area identified by the parcl_id. This value is an integer representing the latest median household income available from relevant census data

parcl_exchange_market.title: Parcl Exchange Market
parcl_exchange_market.description: Specifies whether the geographic area identified by the parcl_id is available as a tradable real estate market on the Parcl Protocol trading platform. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates that the market is active for trading, while 0 indicates it is not

pricefeed_market.title: Pricefeed Market
pricefeed_market.description: Specifies whether a Parcl Labs price feed is available for the geographic area identified by the <parcl_id>. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates that a price feed is active for that market, while 0 indicates that it is not

case_shiller_10_market.title: Case Shiller 10 Market
case_shiller_10_market.description: Specifies whether the geographic area identified by the parcl_id is included in the Case-Shiller 10 index, which tracks the performance of residential real estate in 10 major metropolitan areas in the United States. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates inclusion in the index, while 0 indicates it is not included

case_shiller_20_market.title: Case Shiller 20 Market
case_shiller_20_market.description: Specifies whether the geographic area identified by the parcl_id is included in the Case-Shiller 20 index, which tracks the performance of residential real estate in 20 major metropolitan areas in the United States. It is a boolean value: 1 indicates inclusion in the index, while 0 indicates it is not included

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Data reflects the specific day indicated by the date. Weekly endpoints are indexed on Mondays and become available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

count_price_change.title: Count Price Change
count_price_change.description: Total number of properties within the current for sale inventory that have experienced at least one price change

count_price_drop.title: Count Price Drop
count_price_drop.description: Total number of properties within the current for sale inventory that have experienced at least one negative price change

median_days_bt_change.title: Median Days Bt Change
median_days_bt_change.description: Median number of days between price changes for properties within the current for sale inventory

median_price_change.title: Median Price Change
median_price_change.description: Median dollar value of all price changes observed for properties within the current for sale inventory

median_pct_price_change.title: Median Pct Price Change
median_pct_price_change.description: Median percentage change in price for properties within the current for sale inventory that have observed a price change

pct_inventory_price_change.title: Pct Inventory Price Change
pct_inventory_price_change.description: Percentage of properties within the current for sale inventory that have observed a price change

for_sale_inventory.title: For Sale Inventory
for_sale_inventory.description: Total current count of properties listed for sale on the market. This count is calculated by identifying unique properties that have had a listing event (initial sale listing, relisting, or price change) within the previous 50 days, and have not had any subsequent listing removal events (such as a sale, listing removal, or pending sale) within the same period

parcl_id.title: Parcl Id
parcl_id.description: A unique id for a given geographic market in the Parcl Labs API. Parcl_ids are unique and independent of each other, without any hierarchical structure. For example, the parcl_id for Brooklyn, NY bears no relationship to the parcl_id for the New York Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), even though Brooklyn is a part of the New York MSA

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in format YYYY-MM-DD. Data reflects the full month indicated by the date (YYYY-MM-DD), with updates on the 15th of the following month to include all events from the previous month. For example, data for January ('2024-01-01') is available on February 15th to include January's events. On the 15th of each month, data is revised to incorporate any new events recorded for the specified month after the initial update, ensuring the most accurate reflection of events

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods.

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in format YYYY-MM-DD. Data reflects the full month indicated by the date (YYYY-MM-DD), with updates on the 15th of the following month to include all events from the previous month. For example, data for January ('2024-01-01') is available on February 15th to include January's events. pct_gross_yield.title: Pct Gross Yield
pct_gross_yield.description:
Percent gross yield within a given month, calculated by dividing the annual median rental income (monthly median new_rental_listing price × 12) by the median new_listings_for_sale price, then multiplying by 100 to convert the result into a percentage

NULL: insufficient data

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in format YYYY-MM-DD. Data reflects the full month indicated by the date (YYYY-MM-DD), with updates on the 15th of the following month to include all events from the previous month. For example, data for January ('2024-01-01') is available on February 15th to include January's events. On the 15th of each month, data is revised to incorporate any new events recorded for the specified month after the initial update, ensuring the most accurate reflection of events

purchase_to_sale_ratio.title: Purchase To Sale Ratio
purchase_to_sale_ratio.description:
Investor purchase to sale ratio within a given month, calculated by dividing the number of investor purchases (acquisitions) by the number of investor sales (dispositions).

1.00: Equal numbers of purchases and sales, achieving a 1:1 balance

>1.00: More purchases than sales

<1.00: More sales than purchases

0: No purchases (numerator = 0)

NULL: No sales (denominator = 0)

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

start_date.title: Start Date

end_date.title: End Date
end_date.description: Specifies the end of the query period, inclusive, in ISO 8601 format, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. Defaults to NULL

parcl_property_id.description: Unique property identifier tied to a specific address and unit

event_date.title: Event Date
event_date.description: Specific date the housing event occurred on

event_type.title: Event Type
event_type.description: Type of housing event associated with the property: SALE, LISTING, RENTAL, ALL

event_name.title: Event Name
event_name.description:
Subcategory of event_type, providing more specific details about the transaction event
* Sale event names:
  - SOLD: Transactions conducted at fair market value between unrelated parties
  - NON_ARMS_LENGTH_TRANSFER: Transfers where the buyer and seller share a pre-existing relationship (i.e., identical last names) or the transaction is not conducted at fair market value (price is 0 and not in a Non-Disclosure (ND) state)
  - SOLD_INTER_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER: Transactions between two distinct entities
  - NON_ARMS_LENGTH_INTRA_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER: Transfers within the same entity portfolio
* Listing event names: LISTED_SALE, LISTING_REMOVED, OTHER, PENDING_SALE, PRICE_CHANGE, RELISTED
* Rental event names: LISTED_FOR_RENT, PRICE_CHANGE, DELISTED_FOR_RENT

price.title: Price
price.description: Total transactional price for a housing event. For rentals, the price represents the monthly rate

owner_occupied_flag.title: Owner Occupied Flag
owner_occupied_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the property is owner-occupied (i.e., not owned by an investor) at the time of the housing event.

0 signifies that the property is not owner-occupied

1 signifies that the property is owner-occupied

NULL signifies that the owner status is unknown

new_construction_flag.title: New Construction Flag
new_construction_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the property is new construction at the time of the housing event.

0 signifies that the property is not new construction

1 signifies that the property is new construction

investor_flag.title: Investor Flag
investor_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the property is owned by an investor at the time of the event.

0 signifies that the property is not investor-owned

1 signifies that the property is investor-owned

NULL signifies that the investor status is unknown

entity_owner_name.title: Entity Owner Name
entity_owner_name.description:
The name of the entity that owns the property at the time of the event, if owned by a named large-scale operator.

Possible values include:

AMH

TRICON

INVITATION_HOMES

HOME_PARTNERS_OF_AMERICA

PROGRESS_RESIDENTIAL

FIRSTKEY_HOMES

AMHERST

NULL indicates the property is not currently owned by one of these named entities

current_owner_flag.title: Current Owner Flag
current_owner_flag.description:
Boolean flag indicating if the current owner is the owner of the property at the time of the event

0 signifies that the current owner is not the owner at the time of the event

1 signifies that the current owner is the owner at the time of the event

NULL signifies that the ownership status is unknown

transfer_index.title: Transfer Index
transfer_index.description:
Number of transfers that have occurred over the lifetime of a property at the time of the event. Transfers include any SALE event, which includes:
- SOLD
- NON_ARMS_LENGTH_TRANSFER
- SOLD_INTER_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER
- NON_ARMS_LENGTH_INTRA_PORTFOLIO_TRANSFER

true_sale_index.title: True Sale Index
true_sale_index.description: Number of genuine property sales that results in an actual change of ownership under fair market conditions (SOLD) that have occurred over the lifetime of a property at the time of the event

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in format YYYY-MM-DD. Data reflects the full month indicated by the date (YYYY-MM-DD), with updates on the 15th of the following month to include all events from the previous month. For example, data for January ('2024-01-01') is available on February 15th to include January's events. On the 15th of each month, data is revised to incorporate any new events recorded for the specified month after the initial update, ensuring the most accurate reflection of events

rental_units.title: Rental Units
rental_units.description: Total number of units considered a rental, inferred from ownership and rental market activity, within a specified <parcl_id>

total_units.description: Total number of single_family, townhouse, condo, and other non-land units within a specified <parcl_id>

pct_rental_concentration.title: Pct Rental Concentration
pct_rental_concentration.description: Percentage of total housing units that are considered rental units within a given month, calculated by dividing the number of rental_units by the total_units, then multiplying by 100 to convert this number into a percentage. This metric estimates the rental concentration within a specified <parcl_id> and may potentially overestimate the actual figure

date.title: Date
date.description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format. This field represents the index date, which is the Monday following a complete data capture week that runs from Monday to Sunday. The index date serves as the anchor for aggregating and reporting the data collected during the preceding week (7 day) and also sets the reference point for the rolling aggregation periods of 30, 60, and 90 days ending on this date. For example, if data is captured from 2024-01-01 (Monday) to 2024-01-07 (Sunday), the index date will be 2024-01-08, the Monday immediately following the capture period . Data becomes available for access on the Thursday following the index date. If no data is returned for a specified index date, it signifies that no relevant events were recorded within the specified aggregation periods

rolling_7_day.title: Rolling 7 Day
rolling_7_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 7 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period captures data from the previous Monday to Sunday. For example, if the index date is 2024-03-11 (a Monday), this aggregation period spans from 2024-03-04 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value indicates an absence of data during this period (equivalent to 0)

rolling_30_day.title: Rolling 30 Day
rolling_30_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 30 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a rolling monthly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-02-09 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_60_day.title: Rolling 60 Day
rolling_60_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 60 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period offers a two-month view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2024-01-11 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)

rolling_90_day.title: Rolling 90 Day
rolling_90_day.description: Aggregation period covers a 90 day period immediately preceding the index date. This period provides a quarterly view up to the Sunday before the index date. For example, with an index date of 2024-03-11, this aggregation period includes data from 2023-12-12 to 2024-03-10. A NULL value signifies no observed data within this timeframe (equivalent to 0)
